            <p>In this module, we will learn helpful methods for studying for a test or quiz.</p>
            <h4>Introduction</h4>
            <p>Studying helps us prepare for and do well on tests and quizzes. Sometimes we may find preparing for a test difficult or overwhelming.  These steps and study methods may help us with studying and make the process fun! </p>
            <h4> Lesson</h4>
            <p>While preparing for a test consider these steps:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Determine the content coverage and question format of the exam
                <ul>
                  <li>What is the exam about?</li>
                  <li>Will there be multiple choice, essay questions, free response, fill in the blank?</li>
                </ul>
              </li>

              <li>Organize and Separate the content into parts
                <ul>
                  <li>Separate into different topics or chapters</li>
                </ul>
              </li>

              <li>Identify study strategies:
                <ul>
                  <li>Use Note Cards for definitions </li>
                  <li>Use Mind Maps to organize information </li>
                  <li>Use self testing to pretest yourself by predicting questions that will be on the exam.</li>
                </ul>
              </li>

              <li>Identify the amount of time needed for each strategy
                <ul>
                  <li>How long will it take to complete all the study strategies?</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              
              <li>Summarize, Review, and Reflect the content studied.Â </li>
            </ol>

            <h4>Examples</h4>
            <ol>
              <li>Determine the content coverage and question format of the exam
                <ul>
                  <li>Roman History</li>
                  <li>Multiple Choice and Fill in the blank</li>
                </ul>
              </li>

              <li>Separate the content into parts
                <ul>
                  <li>Roman Religion</li>
                  <li>Roman empire</li>
                  <li>Present Rome</li>
                </ul>
              </li>

              <li>Identify study strategies
                <ul>
                  <li>Mind Maps and Note Cards</li>
                </ul>
              </li>

              <li>Amount of time needed for each strategy
                <ul>
                  <li>About 6 hours</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ol>
