            <p>In this exercise we will learn and practice how to create mind maps and note cards.</p>
            <h4> Mind Map</h4>
            <p><span class="toBold">Description: </span>A Mind Map is a diagram that helps us visually organize information. We can use it to help us study by thinking about topics and how they relate together.</p>
            <p class="toBold"> Instructions: </p>
              <ol>
                <li>On a separate piece of paper, create a mind map for a topic you are learning in history or science. Use the map figure below as a guide.</li>
                <li>Write a main topic in the middle and draw a circle or box around it. A main topic is a big idea or theme (Example: the water cycle).</li>
                <li>Surround the main topic with subtopics. a subtopic is an idea that describes the main topic (Example: for the water cycle, subtopics could be evaporation, condensation, and precipitation</li>
                <li>Draw lines from subtopic to the main topic</li>
                <li>Around the subtopics, jot down supporting points, ideas and examples.</li>
              </ol> 
